      "message": "Given that PictureImage requires a temporary buffer (as discussed in https://skia-review.googlesource.com/c/skia/+/332753), this patch set just draws to an SkCanvas and returns those pixels. This patch set still has a bug, though - if the image is opaque, but the post-process SkPicture adds alpha, the SkBitmap should have alpha. I noticed this while running viewer. To my surprise, the bug didn\u0027t show up everywhere:\n- in DM (config 8888 and gl), the corners look rounded (as I intended, though perhaps incorrectly)\n- in viewer, OpenGL looks the same as DM, but viewing in Raster caught the bug\n\nI simplified the use case and came up with a fiddle: https://fiddle.skia.org/c/a3b0310ac8203b3c357c0c2851dcaf05\n\nGiven that I was essentially lying, by marking the bitmap as kOpaque_SkAlphaType and then putting transparent pixels in it, maybe it\u0027s okay that the we don\u0027t get consistent results?",
